
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gjs` baraye ejra kardan barname-haye JavaScript rooye GNOME estefade mishavad. Yani be shoma emkan mide barname-haye grafikio ba JavaScript benevisid ke ba GNOME desktop integration dashte bashan.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gjs <esme_file.js>`  --> 🚀 Eejra kardan file JavaScript.
    🔹 `gjs -v` --> ℹ️ Namayesh dadane version e GJS.
    🔹 `gjs -c <command>` --> 💻 Eejra kardan yek command JavaScript az terminal.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gjs hello.js

    🔹 Eejra kardan file'e `hello.js`.

    $ gjs -c 'print("Hello, world!")'

    🔹 Eejra kardan command'e `print("Hello, world!")` dar terminal.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gjs -v

    🔹 Version'e GJS rooye system namayesh dade mishe, mesle "GJS 1.72.0".

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gjs` command is used to execute JavaScript programs on the GNOME platform. It allows you to write graphical applications in JavaScript with GNOME desktop integration.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gjs <file_name.js>` --> 🚀 Execute a JavaScript file.
    🔹 `gjs -v` --> ℹ️ Display the GJS version.
    🔹 `gjs -c <command>` --> 💻 Execute a JavaScript command from the terminal.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gjs hello.js

    🔹 Executes the file `hello.js`.

    $ gjs -c 'print("Hello, world!")'

    🔹 Executes the command `print("Hello, world!")` in the terminal.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gjs -v

    🔹 Displays the GJS version on your system, such as "GJS 1.72.0".

